ai.skymind.pipelines.threadpool.tensorflow.conversion.graphrunner

Class GraphRunner

  • java.lang.Object
    • ai.skymind.pipelines.threadpool.tensorflow.conversion.graphrunner.GraphRunner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class GraphRunner
extends Object
implements Closeable
    Runs a TensorFlow session based on zero copy INDArray memory replicated to TensorFlow. INDArray is used to hold the memory while TensorFlow's c bindings are used for running the graph.
    Author:
    Adam Gibson

                   Map<String,TensorDataType> inputDataTypes,
                   Map<String,TensorDataType> outputDataTypes)
        The constructor for creating a graph runner via builder
        Parameters:
        inputNames - the input names to use
        outputNames - the output names to use
        savedModelConfig - the saved model configuration to load from (note this can not be used in conjunction with graph path)
        sessionOptionsConfigProto - the session options for running the model (this maybe null)
        sessionOptionsProtoBytes - the proto bytes equivalent of the session configuration
        sessionOptionsProtoPath - the file path to a session configuration proto file
        graph - the tensorflow graph to use
        graphPath - the path to the graph
        graphBytes - the in memory bytes of the graph
        inputDataTypes - the expected input data types
        outputDataTypes - the expected output data types

        public static org.bytedeco.tensorflow.TF_Tensor castTensor(org.bytedeco.tensorflow.TF_Tensor input,
                                                           TensorDataType from,

        Cast a tensor to another type using the tensorflow c api. This method loads a graph from the classpath from cast_graph/cast_(name of datatype lower case).pb which contains a simple protobuf file with a variant data type tensorflow input place holder named place holder and an output named cast_output.
        Parameters:
        input - the input data
        from - the input data type to cast from
        to - the output data type to
        Returns:
        the casted tensor
